Combine or merge two or more columns based on the realted column

Different types of SQL Joins:
1. Inner Join: Return only matched values from both the tables.
2. Left Join: Returns all the values from left table along with the matched values of right table.
3. Right Join: Returns all the values from right table along with the matched values of left table.
4. Full Join: Retuns all the values from all the tables.
